deck: Past members of the Bloodshot project.
description:
The squad consists of former participants of PRS's Bloodshot Program. All of whom were eventually retired and put on ice at the artificially created habitat known as Bloodshot Island, a hot bed for their experimental weapons tests. Many of the team consists of soldiers and trained fighters who were indoctrinated into the project during the height of every major war fought throughout human history, from Vietnam to the cold war reaching all the way to WWII.

All past Bloodshots had their augmentations upgraded once upon making their way to the island where they'ed been marooned on. To serve as yet another testing phase for Rising Spirit's newest WMD based on technology far superior to their own; Deathmate.

The most recent edition to the team came in the form of the current Bloodshot Ray Garrison. Who had ties with his new adversary in another life when she was the Geomancer, after the project had scrapped the Island causing it to sink into the ocean the B-Squad managed to sail out to safety on a makeshift raft. Wandering into open ocean and trading stories until their rescue by MI-6 operative: Ninjak.
name: Bloodshot Squad

deck: A group with unknown motives outside of making money.
description:
The group is ran by a man named Kragg who wanted to fix a boxing match. Foggy Nelson the district attorney at the time looked into the group after having some suspicion about their motives. Kragg didn't like that Foggy was taking an interest in them and decided to visit him at his office and try to scare him off. Thankfully Daredevil was outside the window listening in and was able to get them to back off.

Daredevil however was not through with group and decided to look more into them himself. He visited their training camp as blind Matt Murdock and learned from his father's former trainer Pop Fenton that this Phoenix group was up to no good and planned to make Kid Gawain, the boxer they recently bought take a fall against Slugger Sloan. Kid Gawain had no interest in taking a fall and made his thoughts known to Kragg. While Kid was walking down the street Phoenix attempted to send a message by working him over but they were fought off by Daredevil who came to Kid's aid.

Later that day Matt and Foggy went to watch the match. Matt made a quick excuse and took off only to knock out Kid using a precise pinch to a pressure point in his neck. He used his amazing sense of touch to recreate the Kids face over his own with makeup. He then entered the ring as Kid. "Kid" then proceeded to destroy Slugger Sloan in the ring only to discover that Kragg had planned to use a machine he smuggled in in the guise of a TV camera to temporary blind Kid during the fight so that he'd lose. Matt already being blind was not effected by the machine and knocked out Slugger Sloan then made a break upstairs to where the machine was fired.

On the way up Fenton, Kid's trainer tossed Daredevil's costume at "Kid" telling him that he figured out that he wasn't the real Kid when he saw the costume and told him to hurry as the real Kid's in trouble. Kid was surrounded by the Phoenix group in his room and charged toward them bravely even though Kragg had a gun drawn on him. Kid was shot and went down, but soon after Daredevil burst in and cleaned up Kragg and the rest of Phoenix. Luckily Kid was going to be okay. Phoenix was then brought to prison what happened after that is unknown.
name: Phoenix

deck: Dark hearted Luchadores who serve Catrina and Mil Muertes.
description:
Origin

Barrio Negro, El Siniestro de la Muerte and Trece, are the Disciples of Death, mysterious luchador wrestlers who seem obsessed with death. Assembled by Catrina to act as enforcers and henchman for Mil Muerte, they prowl and participate in Lucha Underground fighting scene. Originally Catrina and Mil Muerte operated by themselves. However after Catrina seemed to doubt Mil Muerte's abilities, after losses to Fenix, and Catrina assisting Fenix, the two would separate. It would be a ruse however, with Catrina looking to increase the power of Mil Muerte and after a brief disappearance by both, they would return stronger than ever, this time with three new wrestling talents, Barrio Negro, El Siniestro de la Muerte and Trece.

The trio of death obsessed lucha, would target and attack at Catrina's command, and the Trios Champions Son of Havoc, Ivelisse, and Angelico would count among their victims. At one point, the Disciples of Death would challenge the dysfunctional bunch and win the titles off them. This would mirror the success Mil Muerto would continue to have.

Another bizarre objective set by Catrina for the Disciples of Death, would be to gather enough sacrifices, specifically real and raw skulls. These skulls would serve as a base for a macabre and gristly throne for Mil Muerte. Barrio Negro, El Siniestro de la Muerte and Trece would go on a killing spree, slaughtering innocents, to take their heads and skulls, eventually creating Mil Muerte's morbid skull throne. Mil Muerte would use the throne to observe Lucah Underground matches, when he and Catrina would supplant Dario Cueto.

Creation

The trio of characters that form the Disciples of Death, Barrio Negro, El Siniestro de la Muerte and Trece, were created by El Rey Network, for use in Lucha Underground. The team and the characters also appear in the Lucha Underground comics, first appearing in Lucha Underground - Peace Keeper, appearing as the focal point in the following issue, The Throne.
name: The Disciples of Death

deck: Secret society dedicated to ruling the world by covertly controlling the world's oceans.
description:
Origin

N.E.M.O. (Nautical Enforcement of Macrocosmic Order) is a clandestine organization with the objective of secretly rulling the world through control of the oceans. The were founded in 1872 and they have achieved functional control of the seas in 1983.

Creation

N.E.M.O. was created by Aquaman writer Dan Abnett.

Major Story Arcs

The Drowning

N.E.M.O. first appear in Aquaman during DC Rebirth and they free Black Manta from an armored escort, after he was defeated by Aquaman in the attack on Spindrift Station. After some negotiation with Black Jack he agrees to meet with the leader of N.E.M.O.

Using one of N.E.M.O's highly advanced Albatross Stealth Planes they travel to Antarctica where Black Manta meets the Fisher King, leader of N.E.M.O. The Fisher King tries to convince Manta to join N.E.M.O. as an agent but without having any say to the plans and agenda of the organization. Black Manta dissagrees and quickly murders the surprised Fisher King, immediately declaring himself as the new leader of N.E.M.O. and seizing control of the organization.

It is revealed that N.E.M.O. under Fisher King's leadership are responsible for attacking the USS Ponchartrain trying to frame Aquaman and Atlantis.

Black Manta solidifies his control over the organization in a meeting of the leadership in Venice, where he eliminates any opposition with the help of his new second in command Black Jack. N.E.M.O. now moves to announce themeselves to the world as a global power, taking the first steps in eliminating Atlantis and Aquaman before he can find out N.E.M.O.'s agenda.

Resources & Equipment

  • N.E.M.O. are extremely rich having achieved functional control of the oceans and trade over seas since 1983.
  • They possess advanced technology and weapons such as energy rifles.
  • Their main base of operations is a secret location in Antarctica.
  • They have Albatross Stealth Planes that can stay airborne for weeks.
  • They employ trained agents who wear a red uniform with golden masks and can carry on missions such as extracting a prisoner from an armored escort.
  • They employ the services of some of DC's most prominent super scientists such as Dr. Ivo, although they don't know they work for N.E.M.O.

Origin

The Shadow Seven is a group trained master assassins who, like Colin King, were students under the undead monk. Each of whom in the order he taught, which had the backing of an infamous powerful dark mystic, were altered via powerful magics as apart of their tuition in the killing arts. This also serves to aid them in their particular fields of crime and other duplicitous pursuits.

Each of the monks students have a mastery of the physical self that enables them a host of phenomenal if not supernatural capabilities. Likewise their teacher had often erased any traces of their individual memories in order to cover his tracks, leaving blanks in some of his acolytes minds only for them to reassert itself at a later date.
